snippet.textDisplay:
"If I play with my dear one, if I win, my sweetheart is mine. If I lose. I'm still with my dear one" 
This is such a deep line and deeply mystical, paradoxical and full of Truth. The belief in separation (being an individual person) is where this is about, in reality all is one and separation does not exist, everything is Divine and free will doesn't exist (although we might feel we have such a thing- that's the play) , "If I play with my dear one" gives a hint about this. If his (God, Brahman, Allah, The Absolute or Life) game is played right a seemingly individual will turn inwards and realises His own nature, when one (a seemingly separate individual) doesnt do that He is still with his dear One as finally all will come to this oneness. No matter what "His will" be done.
"You have snatched away all trace of me" refers to a seemingly seperate individual who turned inwards and realised his own Divinity.
